<headline>Severe Weather Statement issued May 06 at 2:21PM EDT until May 06 at 3:15PM EDT by NWS Tallahassee</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 300 PM EDT
FOR SOUTHEASTERN IRWIN AND NORTH CENTRAL BERRIEN COUNTIES...
At 221 PM EDT, a severe thunderstorm was located near Ocilla, moving
east at 30 mph.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and quarter size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Hail damage to vehicles is expected. Expect wind damage to
roofs, siding, and trees.
Locations impacted include...
Gladys and Wray.
TORNADO...POSSIBLE
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...1.00 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
<instruction>A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 700 PM EDT for south central
Georgia.
For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
